// GitStore gRPC Git Service contract — v1 (012-smart-http-api revision)
//
// Changes from 010 baseline:
//   - Added `InfoRefs` RPC: returns the ref advertisement for upload-pack or
//     receive-pack without a PACK transfer.
//   - Added `ReceivePack` RPC: client-streaming push; transfers PACK data in
//     chunks to avoid buffering the full packfile in memory.
//   - Added `UploadPack` RPC: server-streaming clone/fetch; streams the PACK
//     response back in chunks.
//   - Added `Service` enum, `InfoRefsRequest`, `InfoRefsResponse`,
//     `ReceivePackChunk`, `ReceivePackResponse`, `UploadPackRequest`,
//     `UploadPackChunk` messages.
//   - `repository_id` field convention (field 15) preserved for all new
//     request messages, consistent with the 010 baseline.
//   - No existing RPCs, messages, or field numbers removed (additive only).
//
// Streaming conventions:
//   ReceivePack (client-streaming):
//     - First chunk: repository_id + ref_commands + first pack_data bytes
//     - Subsequent chunks: pack_data only
//     - Final chunk: is_last = true
//     - On any stream error: git-service discards quarantine atomically
//   UploadPack (server-streaming):
//     - Request: single message with repository_id + full want/have body
//     - Response chunks: sideband-encoded pkt-line bytes, 64 KiB max each
//     - Final chunk: is_last = true

